title: Bug 110566 - Wrong data set result returned when an invalid filter expression 'row[0]' is set
description: When an invalid filter expression 'row[0]' is set, the data set returns incorrect results or a null result set.
OB: The data set returns incorrect results or a null result set when an invalid filter expression 'row[0]' is set.
EB: The data set should return the correct results or generate an error message when an invalid filter expression 'row[0]' is set.
SR:
1. Set an invalid filter expression 'row[0]'.
2. Verify that the data set returns incorrect results or a null result set.
